<font color="#FF0000">MEALS ON WHEELS</font><br>
<tt>Mon Aug 25  9:45:32 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
When we had our reunion I send everyone from our platoon a P-38 aquired from the local Army surplus store for 33 cents. When you think of all the ones we threw away we could have recycled them and retired. <br>
Had a contest to see who would be champ at opening cans, afraid Ed would have won! We would have made him honorary member of Suicide India. <br>
Tried firing the 60 from a chopper, No good. Couldn't sign my signature on Charlie's chest, had to settle for only my initials.<br><br>
Questions<br>
1. How many P-38's came in a C-rat carton?<br>
2. What were the type of meals that came in a carton?<br>
3. How many meals to a case?<br>
4. What was the main course that came with pound cake and peaches?<br>
5. What were the annenities that came with the meals?<br>
6. What were the brand of cigarettes?<br><br>
Answers will be graded as follows<br>
1 Correct Real Vet<br>
2 Correct REMF<br>
3 Correct supply sgt.<br>
4 Correct REAL GRUNT<br>
5 Correct Marine<br>
6 Mamason<br><br>

